Service Availability and Data Durability Constraint

The platform based on Kubernetes, Docker and OpenShift shall ensure a high level of service availability and data durability.

The system shall be designed to achieve high availability by avoiding single points of failure and enabling automatic recovery mechanisms.

In case of failure, the platform shall guarantee:
- Automatic restart of failed components (self-healing)
- Load distribution across multiple instances (horizontal scalability)
- Zero or minimal service disruption for end users

Regarding data persistence, the system shall ensure:
- No data loss in case of application or container failure
- Persistent storage backed by Kubernetes Persistent Volumes
- Database durability and consistency through PostgreSQL mechanisms
- Backup and recovery capabilities for disaster scenarios

The application shall be deployed within the intranet environment, ensuring controlled access and compliance with enterprise security policies.



