Platform Capability and Configuration Responsibility

The selected PaaS platform based on Kubernetes, Docker and OpenShift provides the capability to configure key parameters such as:
- Number of pod replicas
- Resource allocation (CPU and memory)
- Auto-scaling policies
- Persistent storage and volume management

These configuration capabilities enable the system to achieve the required levels of availability and data durability.

The target availability and data durability levels are not intrinsic properties of the platform but are achieved through the correct configuration and deployment strategy of the application components.

The specific strategy to ensure high availability and data durability is described in section 3.4.2.4.

